# File Size And Subcomponents

- Keep source files under 400 lines whenever possible.
- Hard limit: do not create or extend files beyond 500 lines.
- If a file approaches 350-400 lines, extract UI blocks and logic into focused subcomponents/services/helpers before adding more code.
- Prefer splitting by responsibility (view, state, api, mapper, utils) instead of by arbitrary chunks.
- For Angular pages, move inline template/styles into dedicated `*.html` and `*.scss` files early.
- Large repeated UI sections must be standalone/reusable components, not duplicated markup.

## Example

```ts
// BAD: booking-page.component.ts with 520 lines and inline template/styles.
// GOOD: booking-page.component.ts + booking-page.component.html + booking-page.component.scss
// and extracted step-specific blocks into subcomponents when needed.
```
